Generation of an S-function for a subsystem that contains one or more Model blocks detected a configuration parameters mismatch.


The mismatch is due to one of these causes:

A) Before S-function generation, there was a configuration parameter mismatch in the model reference hierarchy of model ''{0}''.

B) S-function generation setup changed configuration parameter settings.


To determine which is the cause in this case, try building the model ''{1}''.

- If the build fails because of a configuration parameter mismatch, then cause "A" applies.

- If the build succeeds, cause "B" applies.


To address cause "A", make the configuration parameters listed below match throughout the model hierarchy and try rebuilding model ''{2}'' until it builds successfully. Once the model builds successfully, try generating the S-Function again. If the S-Function generation fails, address cause "B".


To address cause "B", adjust the parameters of your model hierarchy based on the mismatches described below, so that your hierarchy matches the settings of ''{3}''.
